This paper deals with person re-identification using visible and thermal cameras, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a method for enhancing feature learning, which involves machine learning (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.LG) techniques. The use of triplet loss for training the model also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with security and privacy concerns related to surveillance systems, which could fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
